---
alwaysApply: true
---

- The README.md implementation status table must reflect reality at all times.
- Valid status values:
    🔲 Not Started   — stub only, no logic implemented
    🔄 In Progress   — partially implemented, not all tests pass
    ✅ Complete      — all functions implemented, tests pass, integrated
- When you implement a function in any module, update the status table
  in the same edit session. Do not mark ✅ unless:
    - All public functions in the module have working implementations
    - At least the basic tests for that module pass
    - The module's integration contract output (CSV, JSON, dataclass)
      can actually be produced by running the module
- When a module changes from 🔲 to 🔄 or 🔄 to ✅, add a one-line
  entry to DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md noting the status change.
- The professor should be able to read the status table and know
  exactly what works and what does not — no guessing.
